title: A Double-Blind, Randomized, Placebo-Controlled, Dose Escalating Study to Evaluate the Safety, Tolerability, and Immunogenicity of V950 Formulated on Aluminum-Containing Adjuvant With or Without ISCOMATRIX™ in Patients With Alzheimer Disease
description_brief: The purpose of this study is to test the safety, tolerability and the immune response to an investigational vaccine, V950, with or without ISCOMATRIX™ (IMX).

participantFlowModule.recruitmentDetails: Participants were recruited from 51 sites in Europe, South America and the United States. The primary treatment period was from June 2007 to August 2010, with follow up through January 2012.

outcomeMeasures.description: An adverse event is defined as any unfavorable and unintended change in the structure, function, or chemistry of the body temporally associated with the use of the study drug, whether or not considered related to the use of the product.

outcomeMeasures.title: Geometric Mean Titer (GMT) of Amyloid Beta (Aβ) Peptide 1-40 Specific Antibodies at Month 7
outcomeMeasures.description: The level of Aβ Peptide 1-40 specific antibodies was measured as the geometric mean titer (GMT) one month after the third dose (Month 7) of vaccine using an enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA).
outcomeMeasures.populationDescription: Population consists of all participants who received three doses of vaccine and had no protocol violations. No participants in the V950 50 mcg/IMX 0 mcg group had data for the Month 7 evaluation.

explanation_target: Reason: The intervention is an active immunotherapy (a vaccine) directed at amyloid-β (Aβ) — i.e., it aims to elicit an immune response against Alzheimer’s pathology rather than only improving symptoms, so it fits the disease-targeted biologic category. citeturn0search2turn0search0

Act — trial details: ClinicalTrials.gov listing for NCT00464334 describes V950 administered IM with or without ISCOMATRIX™ adjuvant in a dose-escalation, randomized, placebo-controlled Phase 1 study to evaluate safety, tolerability and immunogenicity in Alzheimer disease patients. Sponsor listed as Merck. (This confirms V950 is a vaccine/adjuvant biologic approach, and that a placebo arm existed.) citeturn0search0turn0search1

Act — drug identity: A review article and trial summaries identify V950 specifically as a multivalent Aβ peptide vaccine that generates anti-Aβ antibodies (targets amyloid pathology). ISCOMATRIX™ is identified as the adjuvant used in formulation. These sources support classifying V950 as a disease-targeted biologic. citeturn0search2turn0search0

Reflect: Classification check — because V950 is an active vaccine targeting Aβ (pathological hallmark of AD) and is a biologic product (peptide vaccine with adjuvant), the correct category is 'disease-targeted biologic'. No information suggests the trial tested a small-molecule disease modifier, a symptomatic cognitive enhancer, or a neuropsychiatric symptom treatment, so alternative categories do not apply. citeturn0search2turn0search0
